system.description: An absolute URI which is the code system from which the selected codes come from.

version.description: The version of the code system that the codes are selected from.

items.description: Specifies a concept to be included or excluded.
Select concepts by specify a matching criteria based on the properties (including relationships) defined by the system. If multiple filters are specified, they SHALL all be true.

name.description: The name of the parameter.

items.description: Business identifier which may be used by other parties to reference or identify the prescription.

dateWritten.description: The date (and perhaps time) when the prescription was written.

patient.description: A link to a resource representing the person to whom the vision products will be supplied.

prescriber.description: The healthcare professional responsible for authorizing the prescription.

encounter.description: A link to a resource that identifies the particular occurrence of contact between patient and health care provider.

reasonCodeableConcept.description: Can be the reason or the indication for writing the prescription.

reasonReference.description: Can be the reason or the indication for writing the prescription.

items.description: Deals with details of the dispense part of the supply specification.

product.description: Identifies the type of vision correction product which is required for the patient.

eye.description: The eye for which the lens applies.

sphere.description: Lens power measured in diopters (0.25 units).

cylinder.description: Power adjustment for astigmatism measured in diopters (0.25 units).

axis.description: Adjustment for astigmatism measured in integer degrees.

prism.description: Amount of prism to compensate for eye alignment in fractional units.

base.description: The relative base, or reference lens edge, for the prism.

add.description: Power adjustment for multifocal lenses measured in diopters (0.25 units).

power.description: Contact lens power measured in diopters (0.25 units).

diameter.description: Contact lens diameter measured in millimeters.

duration.description: The recommended maximum wear period for the lens.

notes.description: Notes for special requirements such as coatings and lens materials.
